  "prompt": "What should you engrave on promise rings?",
  "response": "Engraving promise rings is a beautiful way to personalize them and add a special meaning between you and your partner. Here are some ideas, broken down by category, to help you decide:\n\n**Classic & Romantic:**\n\n*   **Initials:** Your initials, your partner's initials, or both.  (e.g., \"A + B\")\n*   **Date:** The date you met, started dating, or a special anniversary. (e.g., \"10.27.2023\")\n*   **\"I love you\"** (or \"Je t'aime\", \"Te amo\", etc.)\n*   **\"Forever\"**\n*   **\"Always\"**\n*   **\"Eternally\"**\n*   **\"My heart\"**\n*   **\"My love\"**\n*   **\"My everything\"**\n*   **\"Beloved\"**\n\n**Personal & Meaningful:**\n\n*   **Inside Joke:**  A phrase or word that only you two understand.\n*   **Nickname:** A special nickname you have for each other.\n*   **A line from a song:**  A lyric that resonates with your relationship.\n*   **A line from a poem:**  Similar to a song lyric.\n*   **Coordinates:** The location where you first met, had your first date, or a special place.\n*   **\"Yours always\"**\n*   **\"More than words\"**\n*   **\"You're my home\"**\n*   **A significant date:** (Graduation, important achievement, overcoming a challenge)\n*   **A short prayer or blessing** (if you are religious)\n\n**Promise-Specific:**\n\n*   **\"Promise\"**\n*   **\"Always and forever\"**\n*   **\"I promise\"**\n*   **\"A promise kept\"**\n*   **\"One day...\"** (Implying future commitment)\n*   **\"My heart is yours\"**\n*   **\"Growing together\"** (if the promise is about growth)\n*   **\"Building our future\"**\n\n**Minimalist & Symbolic:**\n\n*   **A single word** that represents your relationship (e.g., \"Hope,\" \"Joy,\" \"Faith,\" \"Patience,\" \"Strength\")\n*   **Symbols:**\n    *   Infinity symbol (\u221e)\n    *   Heart symbol (\u2665)\n    *   Celtic knot (representing eternity)\n    *   Bird (symbolizing freedom or growth)\n    *   Religious symbol (cross, Star of David, etc.)\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Ring Size and Font:**  Consider the size of the ring band and the available space.  Thin bands may limit the length of the engraving.  Choose a font that is legible and fits the style of the ring. Discuss font options with the jeweler.\n*   **Jeweler's Advice:**  Talk to your jeweler!  They can advise you on what will fit and look best on your specific rings. They might also have creative suggestions.\n*   **Keep it Short and Sweet:**  Engravings are often small, so choose your words carefully.  The more concise, the better.\n*   **Consider Both Rings:**  You don't necessarily need the same engraving on both rings.  Consider complementary messages or having one ring with a date and the other with initials.\n*   **Proofread!**  Double-check the spelling and dates before finalizing the engraving.  Once it's done, it's permanent!\n*   **What Feels Right:** The most important thing is to choose an engraving that has special meaning for you and your partner.  Don't feel pressured to choose something generic.\n\nUltimately, the best engraving is one that is meaningful and personal to you and your partner.  Think about your relationship, your inside jokes, and what you want the rings to symbolize. Good luck!\n",
